data.text:
Visit the Minneola Farmers Market, every 4th Wednesday of the month from 5 pm to 9 pm. at Minneola City Hall at 800 N. Hwy 27, Minneola.

See you there.

Visitors will have the chance to sample and vote on their favorite treats provided by participating vendors and with a $5 contribution, you can enjoy a tour of the Village, which is a charming collection of historic buildings including a museum showcasing the rich history of Clermont. Children will have a blast participating in a scavenger hunt, making this a family-friendly event.

While youâ€™re at the Village, take the opportunity to learn about the history of beautiful Clermont. The Clermont Historic Village is located at 490 West Ave., at the corner of West Avenue and Osceola Street. For more information, visit the website at clermontvillage.org or call 352-593-8496.

Donâ€™t miss out on this delightful event on August 10â€”join the fun, pick your favorite treat, and explore the historical charm of Clermont!

The 4 Corners Clermont Democratic Club (4CCDC) meets virtually on the 2nd Wednesday of every month from 6:30 to 7:30 pm on Zoom. 4CCDC represents the residents of South Lake County fighting for equal opportunities, families and justice.

Everyone is invited to attend to hear great guest speakers, meet candidates and learn about issues that affect us all. Our next meeting is February 8, 2023. Sign up at: mobilize.us/LakeCountyDEC/event/544981

Facebook.com/4CCDC or Twitter.com/$CCDemClub.
